      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastoplastic model with isotropic hardening and augmented Lagrangian contact demonstrated adequate for F1717 screw-rod constructs in prior literature and FDA guidance.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening (BISO) plasticity with von Mises yield criterion adopted for Ti-6Al-4V components. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) at screw-rod and screw-block interfaces. Model form consistent with FDA-cited Nagaraja 2019 framework and validated against independent experimental data in that study."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from coupon tests on production-lot material; geometric inputs from calibrated CMM measurements of test articles; all inputs traceable to test records.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V ELI elastic modulus (114 GPa), yield strength (827 MPa), and tangent modulus (1.1 GPa) derived from coupon tensile tests on the same material lot as the test constructs. Screw and rod geometry digitised via CMM; nominal CAD used where CMM deviation < 0.02 mm. Input traceability matrix on file. Note: the material property dataset carries a vintage of 2025-11-01, predating the model revision of 2026-02-01; re-characterisation against the revised model geometry is planned for Q2 2026 but has not yet been completed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N ≥ 10 constructs from production-representative lots; dimensional inspection confirms geometry within drawing tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled from production-representative lots. Dimensional inspection (CMM) confirmed all critical dimensions within ±0.05 mm of nominal. Constructs distributed across two independent test laboratories to assess inter-laboratory variability."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conducted under at least two independent loading conditions (e.g., varying offset or load angle) to bound the COU loading space.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 standard configuration (40 mm offset, axial compression-bending). A second loading condition (varied offset) was not included in this campaign. This factor falls below the required level; the gap is acknowledged and a supplementary test series at alternative offsets is planned."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs (geometry, material, boundary conditions) demonstrably equivalent to experimental specimen and test rig configuration.",
      "rationale": "FEA boundary conditions replicate ASTM F1717 fixture kinematics: inferior block fully fixed, superior block constrained to translate axially with 40 mm offset. Material inputs match coupon-tested lot properties. Geometric model derived from CMM data of test articles. Equivalency confirmed by input parameter comparison table reviewed by test laboratory personnel."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison using both absolute percent difference (<10%) and uncertainty-normalised metric E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs.",
      "rationale": "All three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) satisfy <10% difference and E/uval < 1.96. Experimental uncertainty estimated from inter-specimen and inter-laboratory variability (COV 3.1–4.8%); FEA uncertainty from input sensitivity analysis (COV 1.2–2.3%). Combined validation uncertainty used in E/uval calculation per ASME V&V 40 Section 8."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
