      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to the clinical failure mode of interest (fatigue and static overload of pedicle screw constructs).",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing between implant and bone graft; yield force and force at 40 mm displacement bracket the static strength margin against intraoperative and early postoperative overload. These QoIs are specified in ASTM F1717 and are accepted by FDA as relevant surrogates for in vivo mechanical performance."
    },
